<p><em>After monitoring the subject for a ten day period, the subject appeared to develop extrasensory perception and could manipulate small objects without physically interacting with them. The subject often used it unconsciously. For instance, when the subject was reaching for something just out of reach, it would slide slightly closer. Subject is currently contained in a holding cell, further studies on Strain-D are pending. - Assistant Researcher Erickson</em></p>
